&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;                                          BAND 4 SENIOR ADMINISTRATOR&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;SENIOR MANAGEMENT TEAM – DIVISION 6&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;37.5 HOURS PER WEEK &lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;A fantastic opportunity has arisen for a talented and highly enthusiastic senior administrator to join our existing administrative team.  The role requires a dynamic individual who can effectively communicate and can manage a highly detailed and complex workload.   &lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;To be considered for this role you should have a minimum of 2 years recent experience working as a senior administrator, within the NHS or public sector, be educated to GCSE Grade ‘B’ or recognised equivalent in English Language and Mathematics.   You will also possess RSA Stage III or recognised equivalent in Typing/Word Processing, and have excellent I.T. skills and be fluent in Microsoft Office packages. &lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will have an excellent communication style in dealing with all manner of people both internally and external to the organisation.  You will be the first point of contact for the division and have a professional approach at all times.  You will have proven organisational abilities.  You will need to be able to manage and prioritise your own workload, and have the ability to work and respond well under pressure.  You will need to be able to manage extremely busy diaries and organise a fluent, electronic ‘bring-forward’ system for the senior management team in Division 6 at UHB.  You will need to be discrete and have a comprehensive understanding of handling sensitive and confidential matters.  You will need the skills to facilitate and minute take at board-level meetings.   You will have a flexible approach to your work.  Your base of work will be Birmingham Heartlands Hospital however; some cross-site working may be required at times.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information contact Jayne Bovill on 0121-424-0723&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interviews will be held on 16th November 2020 via video link&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
